headline: OpenAI hires former xAI CFO Mike Liberatore as business finance officer
summary: Liberatore, who left xAI in July after just three months on the job, will report to CFO Sarah Friar and work with Greg Brockman's team, which is charged with scaling OpenAI's access to compute, the spokesperson said.  CNBC, which first reported the news, said Liberatore will begin his role on Tuesday.
